The paper deals with capacity limits in wireless communication networks, specifically the interference channel with partial channel state information. This falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. Additionally, the paper discusses techniques such as broadcast channel and genie-aided techniques, which are commonly used in Network Information Theory (cs.NI). The paper also deals with fading networks, which is a topic in Signal Processing (cs.SP) and Wireless Communications (cs.WC). The paper also discusses capacity outer bounds, which is a topic in Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of the derived bound using the entropy power inequality, which is a topic in Statistical Learning (cs.LG).
